    <node id="CONTENT">
      <data key="d0">TABLE</data>
      <data key="d1">The **CONTENT** entity represents a comprehensive catalog of media assets (such as movies and shows) available for streaming on Netflix. It serves as a central table for storing metadata, financial metrics, and distribution details for each unique media title. Key attributes include:  
- A **unique content identifier** to reference individual titles across the system.  
- **Descriptive metadata** like title, genre, duration, release date, and distributor information.  
- **Financial metrics**, specifically cost per stream data and associated currency details.  
- **Distribution and streaming context**, indicating availability for customer streaming and integration with other entities via foreign key relationships.  

This entity consolidates content-related information to support analytics, financial reporting, and operational workflows, ensuring traceability through its unique identifiers and relational links to other data structures.</data>
