      <data key="d1">Based on the provided descriptions for the **SERVICE_PERIOD** entity, the consolidated summary is:

The **SERVICE_PERIOD** is a source column within the invoice table that stores the date range representing the active service duration or billing period covered by an invoice. It is persisted as a text field containing explicitly formatted date range strings (e.g., "2023-01-01 to 2023-01-31"), which denote both the start and end dates of the service timeframe for which the invoice is generated. Due to its textual storage format, this field requires explicit conversion or parsing to derive usable date metrics (such as individual start/end dates or duration calculations) for analytical or operational date-handling purposes. The column fundamentally links billing records to the specific time intervals of service delivery.</data>
